About this item

  • 【Military-Grade Durability】 SOUYIE military sports smart watch boasts a rugged aluminum alloy case and has passed multiple military-grade tests including extreme temperatures, low pressure, dust resistance, and scratch resistance. With a 9H Mohs hardness screen, it’s built to withstand rigorous conditions while maintaining a robust and stylish appearance.
  • 【Stunning 2.02" ULTRA LARGE HD DISPLAY】 SOUYIE smart watch is equipped with a 2.02-inch UHD screen with a resolution of 320*385, which can bring you crystal-clear visual effects. High color accuracy and vivid display ensure an unparalleled viewing experience. Customize your watch with a variety of stylish faces from the DaFit app, or personalize it with your favorite photos.
  • 【Bluetooth Calling & Message Notifications】 Equipped with an integrated microphone and high-fidelity speaker, the SOUYIE Bluetooth smart watch allows you to make and receive calls, manage contacts, and view call logs directly from your wrist. Stay updated with notifications for SMS, Facebook, WhatsApp, Twitter, Instagram, and more, ensuring you never miss an important alert.
  • 【Built-in LED Flashlight】 The SOUYIE tactical smartwatch features a powerful LED flashlight with a range of 6-8 meters, powered by a built-in 500mAh battery for lasting endurance. It's the perfect companion for camping, hiking, or nighttime adventures, lighting your path effortlessly and ensuring you never fear the dark. Depend on its durability for various outdoor activities.
  • 【107 Sports Modes】 Track your workouts with precision across 107 different sports modes. Monitor your steps, distance, and calorie expenditure in real-time to keep your fitness goals on track. SOUYIE fitness tracker smart watch provides detailed activity data to enhance your exercise routines.
  • 【Comprehensive Health Monitoring Smartwatch】 SOUYIE health smartwatch uses advanced optical sensors to accurately monitor heart rate, blood oxygen (SpO2), and blood pressure, helping you understand your health and adjust your lifestyle accordingly. The watch also tracks your sleep (deep sleep, light sleep, awake) and provides comprehensive sleep quality analysis. Additional features like sedentary reminders, hydration alerts, and stress tests help you stay active and maintain peak wellness.
  • 【500mAh Large-Capacity Battery】 The rugged tactical SOUYIE outdoor sports smart watch comes with a 500mAh battery, providing up to 2 weeks of regular use and over 60 days in power-saving mode. The innovative energy-efficient processor and AI smart algorithm optimize task distribution while minimizing power consumption, making it the ideal choice for extended adventures.
  • 【Compass, Barometer & Altimeter】 SOUYIE men's smart watch features a compass, altimeter, barometer sensors, and weather forecasts to help you stay oriented, track altitude and air pressure, and monitor the weather. These functions ensure you stay aware of your surroundings, making it perfect for any adventure.
  • 【Rich Practical Features】 Discover a variety of additional functions, including an AI voice assistant, weather forecast, alarm, remote camera control, music player, stopwatch, phone finder, customizable watch faces, and more. Unlock the full potential of this smartwatch, your reliable companion in everyday life, with endless possibilities.
  • 【Exceptional Support & Warranty】 SOUYIE Smartwatch is compatible with most iOS 9.0 and Android 4.4 or higher smart phones. We offer a 30-day free return policy, a 1-year warranty, and 24/7 customer support. If you have any questions, feel free to contact the SOUYIE customer service team via your Amazon account, and our dedicated team will respond within 24 hours to provide you with the best solution. (Go to Your Orders - Contact Seller).

      • Robert Carnevali
        3.0 out of 5 stars Some very basic features with not as many amenities as you'd think
        Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2025
        I received this for Christmas as a gift and plan on using it for the next year so as to make the giver feel good, but I'll be replacing it. It keeps track of time and date and has a couple of other basic features that are all right, but is lacking in any advanced features. Some of the existing features could have been designed a little better too.

        The body is a single piece of durable metal (or metal-like substance). It's die-cast with ridges, edges, shapes, and grooves that make it look like it's multiple components joined together, but it's just a single piece of metal that's made to look like it's more than it it is. I spent time wondering what the symbols on the four edges were for and realized they were compass markings that served no purpose. I also spent time trying to figure out the purpose of a control on the left edge before I finally realized it was not a control and was just a design shape (it looked like a slider or button). It charges through a USB cable that clings to the back of the watch with magnets. The cable can only attach in a single direction, and the magnets aren't very strong. The tension in the cable often causes it to disconnect, and the watch often needs to be face-down and placed carefully so that the cable will remain affixed.

        It tells time, date, weather, heart rate, oxygen level, barometric pressure, and altitude. It calculates steps taken and calories burned. It has various sports settings that let you choose an activity and time how long you've been doing it. There isn't a way to add new apps to it, you can only customize the appearance and location of existing apps. You can choose different styles for the watch face, with only a couple that are just hands. The digital displays seem rather busy and gaudy, I'm not much of a fan of them.

        The existing controls are mainly function, though some are not thought out well. For example, there is an oxygen level display and a heart rate display. They are two separate displays and you have to go out of the one to call up the other. They are both the result of the same sensor. Any $25 oximeter will show you BOTH heart rate and oxygen level at the same time, but this watch annoyingly separates them. The altitude meter I'm not sure is fully accurate.

        There is a blood pressure monitor that I find frustrating because a watch like this can NOT measure blood pressure. Blood pressure is taken by using a cuff that applies pressure. Therre is no cuff here. This watch always reports high blood pressure for me when I actually have very good pressure.

        There is a handy flashlight feature. An LED on the top edge of the watch shines a small light that can be used when in the dark to move around. It's a nice feature that's made a little less useful because the face of the watch also lights up white to cast extra light. The problem is that you hold your hand up horizontally in front of you (as if you were checking time) so that the LED light is shining forward, and the face is facing upward and is bright what, partially blinding you because it's shining in your face. You can't direct the LED and watch face in the same direction.

        It measures sleep, though I'm not sure of what criteria is used. It does appear to be moderately accurate, though I'm not sure of how well it measures REM and the difference between deep and light sleep.

        When you get a text message on your phone, it displays on the watch, which is very handy. It also lets you receive calls on the watch. An internal microphone and speaker let you talk using the watch, though the volume appears to lean towards the quiet side. Being able to check weather is nice. You can also control your music player on your phone. You can save battery life by only having the watch face display when you turn the watch towards you. Battery life can maybe go for almost two days, and it doesn't take too long to charge (though I haven't timed it).

        It's an OK watch. It lacks the ability to add new apps, and existing ones can be clumsy at times (or worthless and misleading, like the blood pressure one), but it does seem to be durable and it's a very nice price.
